{
  "stem": "5551.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I-- I regret it to this day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I cannot tell his name, no.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this was in the forest next to Gorlice.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When the action-- he described to us a whole action, what is going on in town, with the Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was frightening.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I may talk about this later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he provided us with food, bread and butter and buttermilk and things that-- that peasants have handy, and this vital information.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And eventually, when-- when the-- the murderous action of the Germans was over and everything calmed down in the city, he-- he communicated with those that remained in the city that we trusted.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the decision was made that we should return.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It is now safe.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But we spent, in that forest, about [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] six days.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And if it was not for this Polish man or if he was evil, we could have easily lost our life right there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "By the way, while the history of the Polish is antisemitic-- that is well-established-- it was actually rooted by the teachings of the Catholic Church.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was the main ingredient in feeding the antisemitism in Eastern Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But by a-- by a-- by a strange twist, of-- of-- made by Germans, themselves, they became, in a certain way, allied, since the brutality of the Germans [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] was directed not only at the Jews but at the Poles, as well.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And now, suddenly, the Jews and the Poles had a mutual enemy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It is apparently for that reason that I was repeatedly helped by Polish people.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
